ise for assistance when it is essential \u2022 Report irregularities inform violators of policy and procedures & restraining trespassers \u2022 Control traffic by directing drivers \u2022 Complete reports by recording observations, information, occurrences and surveillance activities; interviewing witnesses; obtaining signatures \u2022 Ensure that the equipment under own use is in a working condition through preventative maintenance \u2022 Ensure the security, safety and well-being of all personnel, visitors and the premises \u2022 Provide excellent customer service \u2022 Adhere to all company service and operating standards \u2022 Remain in compliance with local, provincial and national government regulations \u2022 Respond to emergencies to provide necessary assistance to employees and customers \u2022 Protect the company\u2019s assets relative to theft, assault, fire and other safety issues \u2022 Follow procedures for various initiatives, including fire prevention, property patrol, traffic control and accident investigations Skills and Competencies Skills: \u2022 Verbal & written Communication \u2022 Interpersonal Skills \u2022 Surveillance Skills \u2022 Reporting Skills \u2022 Risk identification Knowledge: \u2022 Application of security processes \u2022 Basic knowledge of Emergency Management (Fire Inspection Procedures, Bomb threat) \u2022 Evacuation procedure \u2022 South African security legislation \u2022 Safety Management \u2022 Health and Safety Act & COIDA Qualifications Grade 11/12 or an equivalent qualification \u2022 PSIRA registration \u2022 Driver\u2019s license an added advantage \u2022 Fire Arm Competency (business use) and advantage \u2022 A clear criminal record Apply Now South Africa United StatesCanada ArgentinaAustraliaBelgiÃ«BrasilDeutschlandEspaÃ±aFranceIndiaIrelandItaliaMÃ©xicoNederlandÃsterreichPortugalSchweizSouth AfricaSverigeUnited KingdomÐ Ð¾ÑÑÐ¸Ñíêµ­ä¸­å½æ¥æ¬ Â© 2020 SH Inc. | Privacy | TermsÂ |Â Privacy Center"
